Description of the MR_base_european_unrelated

This is restricted to only white european unrelated people, using QCed_European and exclusion_list

eid
UK Biobank participant identifier.

PC1–PC10
First ten genetic principal components used to adjust for population structure.
Created by CEU in house on the european restricted data only

ages
Baseline age at assessment.
Derived from year and birth month, then mean-centred

agesq
Squared term of centred age (ages²).
Derived variable 

bmi
Body Mass Index at baseline.
Underlying field: 21001-0.0 (“Body mass index”).

neversmoker
Indicator for never-smoked status.
Usually derived from fields 20116-0.0 (“Smoking status”)
Value = 1 for “Never”, else 0.

assessment_centre
Code for the assessment centre at which the baseline visit occurred.
Underlying field: 54-0.0 (“Assessment centre code”).

sex
Biological sex as recorded by UK Biobank.
Underlying field: 31-0.0 (“Sex”).

townsend
Townsend deprivation index at recruitment (higher = more deprived).
Underlying field: 22189-0.0 (“Townsend deprivation index at recruitment”).